Symposiums on Kim Jong Il's immortal exploits
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- A symposium of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces took place at the April 25 House of Culture on Tuesday on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee  of the Worker's Party of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present there were Jo Myong Rok, director of the general political department of the Korean People's Army, Kim Il Chol, Minister of the People's Armed Forces, and others.   Speakers said at the symposium that Kim Jong Il set a worldwide example in the building of the socialist ruling party and strengthened and developed the people's army into an army of the party of Juche type.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It was stressed at the symposium that all the officers and men of the KPA are absolutely obeying only the orders and instructions of the Supreme Commander and devotedly fulfilling them on the principle of absoluteness and unconditionally and the KPA is demonstrating its might as ranks of human bombs that are devotedly defending the party and the leader in the first line and as a matchless army with strong idea and faith.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The symposium underscored the need to perform a new miracle and feats in defending the socialist motherland as firm as an impregnable fortress and building a powerful nation.   A similar symposium was held by educational workers on June 14.

Military attaches corps visits different places
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited the tower of the Juche idea in Pyongyang on Tuesday on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee  of the Worker's Party of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Being briefed on the fact that the tower was wonderfully built as a monumental edifice under the far-reaching plan and energetic guidance of Kim Jong Il to hand down to posterity the revolutionary idea and undying feats of the President Kim Il Sung, the guests looked round the tower and groups of sculptures.    Then they mounted the tower balcony and enjoyed a bird's eye view of Pyongyang which underwent a grandiose and splendid change.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Earlier,  the military attaches corps visited the metro construction museum. 
   The guests went round with keen interest the mementos and materials on display, being briefed on the fact that Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il initiated and wisely led the metro construction.

Anti-north confrontation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- Chon Yong Thaek, chief of the "Intelligence Service" of South Korea, in his recent commemorative address marking the foundation anniversary of the service blustered "the north has a greed for communizing the south" and the "service should not slacken vigilance", according to a news report.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His deliberate and premeditated sedition for confrontation with the north is a criminal outcry that insults the north and throws a wet blanket over the ardent desire of the fellow countrymen for great national unity.
   His remarks stemmed from a base ruse to slander the north, tarnish its image and justify an ulterior intention to realize their ambition for "unification under the system of liberal democracy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   While at the "ministerial post of national defence", he went the length of proclaiming the north as the "principal enemy" and made himself infamous as a hideous anti-north confrontation that incited a fever of war against the north.
   No sooner had such a war hawk been appointed as the chief of the service than he officially agitated an all-out confrontation with the north. How can we tolerate him?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The point is that the chief executive of South Korea, instead of removing such a devil, appointed him to the post of the "chief of the Intelligence Service," an anti-north plot-breeding center. This proves once again that the South Korean chief executive intends to further aggravate the inter-Korean relations and block peace and peaceful reunification at any cost.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If he truly wants to improve the north-south relations, he should oust such an anti-north confrontation as Chon Yong Thaek and dissolve the service without delay.
   Chon Yong Thaek will have to pay dearly before the nation that is waiting for a chance to take its revenge on him.

Great thinker and theoretician
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- Korean-style socialism is dynamically advancing along the road it has chosen by itself.
   Such an advance is unthinkable apart from the ideological and theoretical activities of General Secretary Kim Jong Il, who has  confidently led the Korean revolution and construction along the road of Juche while working at the Worker's Party of Korea Central Committee  over the last 35 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His energetic ideological and theoretical activities resulted in his publication of many monumental works which give perfect answers to questions  raised by the times and revolution and which are of epoch-making significance in the ideological and theoretical development of mankind.   He authored and published  more than 890 important works in 30 years from June, Juche 53 (1964) to June, Juche 83 (1994). 
   This means he published an annual average of 30 works and theses.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Typical of them is the celebrated work "On the Juche Idea" (March 1982)  which fully reflects his political idea and method.   In the work, he raised the fundamentals of philosophy with the people as a center on a fresh basis and advanced a unique and revolutionary philosophical principle that man is the master of everything and decides everything.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work gives unique definitions to the socio-historical outlook with the position and role of the popular masses as the main and the principle and method  of guidance in the revolution and construction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    He further developed and enriched the Juche idea in "On Some Problems of Education in the Juche Idea" (July 1986), "On Having a Correct Viewpoint and Understanding of the Juche Philosophy" (October 1990), "On Establishing the Juche Outlook on the Revolution" (October 1987) and other works.   The Juche idea has thus become a sole guiding idea of accomplishing the human cause of independence, which is universally recognized by the world for its truth, validity and invincible vitality.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building" (October 1992), "Let Us Resolutely Defend through Generations the Political and Ideological Unity and Purity of the Party" (October 1976) and other works published by him  serve as a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon in strengthening and developing the WPK into an invincible revolutionary party.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In recent years alone, he published "Socialism Is a Science", "the Worker's Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" and "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation" and other works, making it possible for the Korean revolution to advance dynamically along the road of victory  despite the worldwide political turmoil.

Priority to military affairs
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- Military affairs must be given primary importance for the accomplishment of the socialist cause that is inevitably accompanied by acute confrontation with imperialism, stresses an article issued today jointly by the newspaper Rodong Sinmun and the magazine Kulloja, organs of the Worker's Party of Korea Central Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the WPK's policy of giving priority to the army, the article says:   We do not hide from anybody the fact that we have put forward military affairs because they are of utmost importance in realizing the idea of "the people are my god," an idea of defending to the last the destiny of the people with high sense of responsibility.
   The stand of the WPK that gives priority to the army in a just and fair manner will remain unchanged in the future, too.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Short-sighted approach to military affairs is a very dangerous element in socialist politics. Neglect of national defence can never be allowed in socialist politics.   With the Cold War ended, the imperialists are resorting to a more brigandish logic of strength. Countering strength �@with strength and arrogant use of arms with merciless punishment is a way of defending the destiny of the country and the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The last card that is effective in fierce diplomatic confrontation is always one's solid political and military potential and confidence in victory based on it.
   Giving priority to military affairs is not a tactical issue but a strategic issue related to the destiny and future of the revolution. The revolutionary line of giving priority to the army must be maintained whether the situation is strained or relaxed.
   Deviation from the revolutionary principle of giving priority to the army means death.

S. Korean warships in N. Korea waters again
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- The South Korean authorities today infiltrated warships into the north side's territorial waters off its west coast, military sources reported.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  At around 08:00 seven warships of South Korea intruded in battle array deep into the north side's territorial waters off Kangryong county, South Hwanghae Province. Later, they were joined by four more ships at around 08:30. Worse still, brasshats of the "ROK" army ordered their group of warships in waters off Yonphyong islets to secure in advance the "destruction" area and rapidly go into "charge" and fire at patrol ships of the navy of the Korean People's Army, if they move on a patrol duty.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On this instruction the enemy's warships intruded into the north side's territorial waters and desperately attempted to intentionally disturb our navy ships on a routine duty.   This provocation is now leading Korea to a touch-and-go situation in which a war might break out any moment.

S. Korean authorities' military provocations�@flailed
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 16 (KCNA) -- The spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland released a statement today denouncing the South Korean authorities for bringing the situation of the country to a hair-trigger crisis by committing reckless military provocations against the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement says:   Their grave military provocations came at a time when the U.S.,  having changed "operation plan 5027," a war scenario for aggression on the DPRK, into a more bellicose one, finished off its preliminary war, a test war in Yugoslavia under the simulated condition of emergencies on the Korean peninsula.   This shows that preparations of the South Korean authorities for a war of aggression on the north have entered into the stage of its ignition.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We cannot but take a particularly serious view of the South Korean rulers' military provocations in the west sea because they are being committed at a time when conditions are maturing for reconciliation and cooperation between the north and the south and authority-to-authority dialogue is imminent.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Our Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, in the name of the entire nation, vehemently denounces the South Korean authorities for bringing the situation of the country to the brink of war and worsening the inter-Korean relation as never before, branding the reckless moves as a premeditated provocation intended to bar a new phase of detente and dialogue and as a deliberate move aimed at igniting a war against the north under the patronage of the U.S. war hawks.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is entirely thanks to the patience and self-restraint of our people's army that reckless military provocations by the South Korean authorities have not developed into an all-out war.   However, there is a limit to our patience.   The U.S. and their stooges must clearly know that if they finally unleash a new war, the aggressors and provokers will be burned to death in the flame kindled by themselves.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean authorities must apologize for the military provocations at once and put an immediate end to the false propaganda aimed at building up the public opinion that the responsibility for the incident rests with the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We strongly warn that the South Korean authorities cannot escape from the responsibility for worsening the inter-Korean relations and bringing the situation of the country to the brink of war.
   We solemnly declare that we will restrict or suspend Pyongyang visits of South Koreans and their contacts with us for the time being in view of the serious situation created by the South Korean authorities.
